<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-11-06T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-11-06T11:00:00-05:00" n="303" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d303">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">125.655/35: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul General at London</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Skinner</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-11-06T16:00:00+00:00"><hi rend="italic">November 6,
                                        1922—4 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received November 6—2:26
                                p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>From Johnson:</p>
                        <p>I returned from Newcastle where I found nothing to change view expressed
                            in my message transmitted by Embassy on October 6. Sailing 9th <hi rend="italic">President Harding.</hi></p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Skinner</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>